commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Nurse, no run oh dear that's poor fielding. Looks like Sharaf. West Indies have a mix-up as the batsman pushes in front of midwicket and doesn't respond to the non-striker's call. They're both running to the same end. The fielder swoops in, picks it up and lets rip a thunderous throw at the striker's end that the keeper can't catch. Meanwhile, Nabi has his face in his hands at the other end

commentary: Gayle to Mohammad Shahzad, OUT and he's got him! Oh this is...comical, really. Shahzad is sulking like he's been mankaded after facing bodyline bowling for four hours. But the truth is, it's just extremely slow bowling that has completely suckered him. Another loopy length ball from Gayle. Shahzad lines up, then decides to step out. Yorks himself and chips it straight to mid-off. Gayle is bemused. Shahzad shrugs...then pulls out a big celebration just outside the dressing room that hasn't caught Phil Simmons' imagination...absolute Under-14s stuff this!

commentary: Gayle to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs and that's it! Back-to-back sixes to finish this off. Important moment in Afghanistan's history and progression as a top side. Comes down the track and goes big down the ground. Skews it off the outside of the bat but the power on that shot will do
